id: pm-eltf
title: Extract shared test item factories for command specs
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: many command specs copy a createTask/createSeedItem helper that shells through pm create with the same long flag list, then extracts json.item.id. The widened duplicate scan found the same 10-line create sequence across at least 9 files including tests/integration/task-lifecycle-aliases.spec.ts:5, tests/unit/comments-command.spec.ts:16, tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts, tests/unit/restore-command.spec.ts, tests/unit/delete-command.spec.ts, tests/unit/beads-command.spec.ts, tests/unit/notes-learnings-command.spec.ts, tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts, and tests/unit/test-command.spec.ts. This is distinct from pm-7rlp, which targets test runtime performance and CI matrix duplication rather than fixture boilerplate. Fix by adding a shared tests/helper item factory with overridable title/type/status/metadata defaults and migrating repeated local helpers where that does not hide test intent."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: code-quality,dedup,tests
created_at: "2026-05-22T18:54:16.326Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-22T18:54:16.326Z"
author: codex-duplicate-audit
acceptance_criteria: Shared test helper covers common create-item setup with explicit overrides; repeated long createTask/createSeedItem blocks are removed from affected specs; migrated tests still make command-specific setup obvious; targeted unit/integration specs and pnpm build pass.
parent: pm-rnpb
